                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1599072448202-does-completing-an-accessibility-accommodation-request-guarantee-me-a-spot-in-residence-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#e40eab0c-90a7-4fd4-bef1-61ab82bb6833" href="#accordion-content-1599072448202-does-completing-an-accessibility-accommodation-request-guarantee-me-a-spot-in-residence-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1599072448202-does-completing-an-accessibility-accommodation-request-guarantee-me-a-spot-in-residence-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Does completing an Accessibility Accommodation Request guarantee me a spot in residence?
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1599072448202-does-completing-an-accessibility-accommodation-request-guarantee-me-a-spot-in-residence-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1599072448202-does-completing-an-accessibility-accommodation-request-guarantee-me-a-spot-in-residence-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1599072448202 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="b16e8c47-fad8-4b04-9caf-969646313d8e" >

    <p>No, an Accessibility Accommodation Request Form does not guarantee a spot in residence. A request for admission to residence will be considered only if a student would otherwise not be able to attend Ryerson without living in residence, as determined by Ryerson University. </p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#b16e8c47-fad8-4b04-9caf-969646313d8e");});</script></div>

